{
  "stem": "4361.5",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We didn't know what was going on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And this time, you could hear a sigh, you could hear it when this woman sang the",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it must have been that that made me say no.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] I did not think it through.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I did not, because he could have beaten me to death.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But for once, I felt I can refuse something which goes against my grain.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was the only moment that I think back while I was in Auschwitz that I did what I'm glad I did.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's not that I did anything bad or anything good.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was just a cog in the wheel.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I did something beyond what was expected of me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "By whom?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By everybody else, certainly by the SS, certainly by the Amalek, certainly by the evil person, certainly by he who wanted to destroy me, first destroy me, humiliate me, take away my identity, make me into a nothing.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And food-- food, the most exciting, the most potent thing in Auschwitz, because food was life in a way.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Food was power, but in that case, that Yom Kippur, it was not morality.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, that's how I understand it today.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I assure you then, I couldn't think.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I just knew I wanted to lick-- at least to have the taste of that thick soup, and I wasn't going to do it.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
